Flamengo announced club board will hold a press conference tomorrow at 10 AM (Brazil time) to reveal the details of Paquet&aacute;&rsquo;s transfer to Milan [<br />
@gustavodaglobo<br />
]

Romagnoli on Gattuso to Sky: &quot;We have absolute confidence in him. When he arrived he gave us so much, all his determination, all his personality and he is really a person of heart. He has always been on our side, so we would die for him and the whole team is convinced of this.&quot;<br />
<br />
Romagnoli on Musacchio and Caldara: &quot;Mateo is doing great things and Mattia is recovering and can help us. Caldara needs to stay calm. He is young and has time. We are waiting for him with open arms. We showed him that when he arrived and should only think about recovering.&quot;

Spindel: &ldquo;I think from a sporting point of view, for Paquet&aacute;&rsquo;s career, structure and for being in a city that has always welcomed Brazilians, this will be a good move for him and for Flamengo.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Spindel: &ldquo;I flew on October 6 to Milano to conclude the negotiations. I was very well received by Leonardo, Maldini and Leonardo&rsquo;s assistants. Everyone welcomed us very well. Paquet&aacute;&rsquo;s agent had no commission for the negotiation and this was a positive gesture on his part.&rdquo;

Q: Rumors circulating in the Spanish media that Real Madrid could hijack the deal and sign Paquet&aacute;, could this happen?<br />
<br />
Spindel: &ldquo;Flamengo have received nothing.&rdquo;

